// Go workspace pinning the two modules in this repo:
//
//   - .                          — github.com/clearcompass-ai/ledger
//                                  (the Ledger sequencer + supporting cmds).
//   - ./cmd/standalone-witness   — github.com/clearcompass-ai/standalone-witness
//                                  (the witness daemon — physically separate
//                                  module so it cannot import Ledger code).
//
// The two modules share NOTHING beyond the SDK
// (github.com/clearcompass-ai/attesta) which both pin to the same
// version. CI runs `go build ./...` from the repo root, which
// honours this workspace and builds both modules together.
//
// To break the workspace temporarily (e.g., to confirm the witness
// can be built standalone with no awareness of the Ledger):
//
//	GOWORK=off go build ./cmd/standalone-witness/...
//
// That run resolves attesta from cmd/standalone-witness/go.mod alone
// — and would fail loudly if the witness daemon ever introduced a
// stray import of github.com/clearcompass-ai/ledger/*.

go 1.25.7

use (
	.
	./cmd/standalone-witness
)
